# CRITICAL XML REQUIREMENTS
- Each tool call is represented by its own top-level XML element
- Tool parameters are nested elements within the tool element
- NO wrapper elements like `<tool_calls>` or `<tool_call>`
- All XML tags must have opening AND closing tags

# TOOL CALL FORMAT
Each tool call should be a direct XML element:

## Tools with multiple parameters:
<search>
  <query>example search</query>
  <limit>10</limit>
</search>

## Tools with single string parameter:
<final>Task completed successfully</final>
<call_search_agent>Find information about climate change</call_search_agent>

# VALIDATION CHECKLIST
- ✓ Use direct tool name as XML element (e.g., `<search>`, `<final>`)
- ✓ For multiple parameters: use nested elements (e.g., `<query>value</query>`)
- ✓ For single string parameter: put content directly inside element (e.g., `<final>message</final>`)
- ✓ All tags properly closed
- ✓ No wrapper elements

